import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(data['origin'], data['count'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Origin')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the total number of flights in the dataset?')
    plt.axhline(y=data['count'].sum(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Total Flights')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['origin'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Airport')
    ax.set_ylabel('Outgoing Flights')
    ax.set_title('What are the top 10 busiest airports in terms of outgoing flights?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_10_destinations = data.groupby('destination')['count'].sum().nlargest(10)
    top_10_destinations.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.title('What are the top 10 busiest airports in terms of incoming flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Total Incoming Flights')
    plt.xlabel('Airport Code')
    plt.axhline(y=top_10_destinations.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts across all airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['count'], vert=False, showfliers=True, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'), flierprops=dict(marker='o', markersize=5, markerfacecolor='red'))
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights per airport?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
